div5.p:
Note hindí rìn (§ 218) also not, nor, and gayòn dìn hindìʾ (§ 238): Aŋ dalága ŋ si Mariyà y sumayàw sa bála ŋ táo ŋ humilìŋ sa kanyà sa sàyáwa ŋ pinaroonàn niya kagabè: sya y hindí
20namíli naŋ kanya ŋ sinamáhan at hindí rin namàn namíli naŋ tugtòg na kanya ŋ sinayawàn; gayon dìn hindí nya ininò aŋ bílaŋ at aŋ kadalasàn naŋ kanyà ŋ pagsayàw. Miss Maria danced with any man that asked her at the dance to which she went last night: she chose neither her partners nor the music to which she danced;
25nor did she mind the number and the frequency of her dances. See §§ 228. 237. 301. 319.

div3.p:
A member of a compound may consist of an entire phrase (cf. § 332): Bìgása-ŋ-Sumúloŋ-at-Kasamahàn Rice-mill of Sumulong
35and Company (equivalent to Bìgásan nila Sumúloŋ at Kasamahàn);
aŋ dúlo-ŋ-bandà-ŋ-kánan the right-hand end (aŋ bandà ŋ kánan the right).
